-- Colombia Stocks: Ecopetrol, Pacific Rubiales Energy Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-07-09T20:45:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/colombia-stocks-ecopetrol-fabricato-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  was little changed at 13,713.28 while the
Colcap Index slid 0.4 percent to 1,660.33.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates the
country’s largest oil field, gained 1.6 percent to 40,700 pesos.
Crude rose for the first time in three days in  New York .  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  ,  Colombia ’s largest oil company,
fell 0.2 percent to 4,990 pesos. Ecopetrol said the army is
securing an area in the southern province of Putumayo after its
OSO pipeline was sabotaged yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
